England’s Covid R rate remained steady, according to the latest government figures. The UK Health Security Agency said on Friday the reproduction number is between 0.8 and 1.0 - the same as last week. If R is greater than 1 the epidemic is generally seen to be growing; if R is less than 1 the epidemic is shrinking. East of England - 0.8 to 1.0 (unchanged) London – 0.9 to 1.1 (up from 0.8 to 1.0) Midlands – 0.8 to 1.0 (unchanged) North-east and Yorkshire – 0.8 to 1.0 (unchanged) North-west – 0.8 to 1.0 (unchanged) South-east – 0.8 to 1.1 (up from 0.8 to 1.0) South west – 0.8 to 1.0 (up from 0.7 to 1.0)